text: Mark Moseley (born December 10, 1964) is an American voice actor, stand-up comedian and singer-songwriter. He has appeared in a variety of movies, television shows and video games. He is probably best known as a voice double for actors such as Eddie Murphy, Patrick Stewart, Arnold Schwarzenegger, Patrick Warburton and Robin Williams.
